Oct 8 2009 	Very Nice Old-Style Hotel	When you first walk in the front entrance to the hotel, the first thing you see is the grand dining room with the high glass ceiling with a huge chandelier hanging down in the middle. The whole hotel has that 1930's-1940's feel to it. All the hallways are wide and the rooms (at least the one we were in) have high ceilings. The room size was decent. The bath was a bit small and nothing fancy. The bed was OK, but not the Heavenly Bed that I have had at other Starwood properties. Our room faced Market Street, which can be a little noisy, but it wasn't that bad. If you can get one that doesn't face Market, that would probably be advisable. The location is great as Union Square is just blocks away along with all the shopping you want. The Montgomery Street station for BART/MUNI is on the same corner, so it is convenient to take BART from the airport as you walk right out of the station and walk right into the hotel (the $8 BART ride is much cheaper than a cab or shuttle). The historic streetcar line also runs down Market with a stop right outside if you want to take it down to the Wharf. We didn't have a car, so I can't speak to parking, but there is a garage right across the street next to the best little sandwich counter (you'll see the line out the door). Overall the service was great. The doormen out front were helpful, but not pushy like some can be. The location was the key for me as it is in a busy area in the middle of the action.	
