Sep 20 2009 	Good hotel but not a great value	The Palace is a very nice hotel. It is in a great location. Within a short walk of the Ferry Building, Union Square, and Chinatown. Also, it is across the street from the Montgomery St. BART station, making it very easy to get in from the airport or travel to the East Bay. The rooms, while not enormous, are very nicely furnished and clean.Now the downside...This hotel has a very high opinion of itself. Sure, it is a very nice hotel. The ballroom is incredible, but charging more than $30 for an average breakfast is outrageous. A concierge who scoffs when you ask for an inexpensive dinner option seems uncalled for. And a $100 security charge which they leave on your credit card for up to a week after your stay is completely unnecessary, especially when they don't tell you about it or ask for you to authorize it.In the end, this is a very good hotel but you can probably do better and maybe even get a room with a view.	
