Sep 5 2009 	A Great Stay at a Great Hotel	My family and I stayed at the Palace Hotel August 22-27, 2009. Like everyone else who has seen the negative comments about this hotel, especially about the noise factor, I was a little apprehensive before we arrived there, but most of the negative comments turned out to be in my opinion, unfounded. It is a beautiful old, classic hotel in a great central location. The public sitting area was a bit small considering the size of the hotel but that meant nothing to us. It is nothing short of a great historical place. We booked a junior suite for a great price through Expedia and had no problem with room size which was approximately 450 sq. feet. Housekeeping did an excellent job and the nightly turndown service was a great touch. We heard absoutely no noise at all from adjacent rooms or the hallway. The AC could have been a little better but we were able to open the windows and remain very comfortable for the whole stay. As for people writing about problems with wireless internet, I have Verizon mobile broadband and had no problems with connectivity. The kids really enjoyed the pool which was much larger than I expected. The pool was also very clean so I don't know why people would write to the contrary. We only used the hotel parking lot for 2 of the five nights since we found parking directly across from the hotel right on the street. We left the car there for the whole weekend which is allowed and found a cheap nearby lot afterwards but only used for 1 day becaiuse it did not have in-out parking. The number 5 bus is right across the street and that was main mode of transportation to Fishermans Wharf where we ended up a few of our nights there. For anyone travelling with a family, I highly recommend the Muni Passport which can save quite a few bucks on an extended stay. I would definately stay at the Palace again and to get the get best deal, you should check out the travel sites, because the Starwoods site does not seem to offer any decent bargains without having to pay fully non refundable rates. Atl least with the travel sites, you wil be only penalized 1 night for cancellations in most circumstances.	
