Sep 12 2008 	Old World Style	I stayed at The Palace for seven days during a business trip in mid-August 2008. The large building takes up a city block and appears to be about a century old - from a time of the grand hotels. Given its age it is well-maintained and has been updated appropriately. The classic architecture is rife with detail and the decor is stately without being snooty.I took a cab from the airport so can't comment on parking. But, the bell staff and check-in personnel were professional and friendly, getting me to my room quickly and offering to provide advice on restaurants, etc., if needed. My 6th floor room ($260/night including taxes) faced Market Street and was comfortably appointed including a personal safe, a flat screen HD TV and small refrigerator, but no mini bar. As an older hotel, the room was a little smaller than many 4-star+ hotels and closet space was limited but it was nicely appointed with high ceilings, a dresser, a good sized desk and a feaux-antique chair and ottoman.The king bed was very comfortable (the Sheraton Heavenly bed) and the air conditioning worked well on the rare occasion it was needed. The room was generally clean, although based on the residue on the floor-to-ceiling bathroom shutters it appeared that no one had dusted them in quite some time. The room was also noisy at times. To a certain extent this is to be expected in a downtown hotel but the walls are thin and I could clearly hear the details of phone calls occurring in rooms across the hall and over the TV. Also, on two nights, I was kept awake by the sound of diesel engines as heavy machinery raised supplies to the upper floors of a renovation across the street at around 3:00 am. (The view is not that special so if quiet is important to you, ask for a room on the hotel interior.) The bathroom was reasonably spacious with 1920's style tiling and sink and a nice glass-enclosed shower, but no bath tub and limited storage area for my toilet kit. The soaps and other toiletries provided were high quality and the towels were nice and thick. I had a room service dinner on a couple of nights during my stay. Neither was remarkable and I would only recommend this in a pinch. I did not sample the restaurants in the hotel, but they appear to be high-end. There are also a number of highly-rated dining choices within walking distance.I enjoyed my stay at The Palace. The bygone-era charm with expected updates made this an interesting stay that I will remember. Having said that, if the firm had not picked up the tab I'd probably have been less impressed.	
