Jul 10 2008 	Top Notch Hotel Great Service	We stayed at the Palace Hotel during the 4th of the July Weekend and it was a very pleasant experience. As most people have said in their reviews, the hotel has a classy elegant feel to it. the lobby is very nice. The garden court is beautiful. The rooms are spacious and have great high ceilings with a big flat screen tv. The only bad thing about the rooms was that the walls were pretty thin. i could hear people talking in the next rooms. But it wasn't loud enough to keep me awake at night. The hotel is also within walking distance to union square so it's close to all the shops and restaurants. And the hotels is just a few steps away from public transportation such as the bart, trolley, bus, etc. But it's not close to any of the major tourist attractions such as fisherman's wharf, golden gate bridge, lombard st., etc. But we rented a car so it was fine. The best part of the hotel in my opinion was the staff. Everyone was so friendly and helpful. The bellmen and valets would always greet you and ask if you needed anything from water to directions. For example, whenever we were waiting for our car from the valet, as soon as we took out our maps, a staff member would come over right away and ask if we needed help with directions. The front desk was also great. The cleaning staff was very friendly. And the concierge was very helpful. If you're looking for a fun, hip hotel this is not the place for you. This an elegant, classy, refined hotel with great service. i would not hesitate to come back.	
