Jul 2 2008 	A Hotel with Character	My girlfriends and I stayed at the Palace hotel from June 27th to 30th. All in all, it was a very pleasant stay. I will say that the hotel looks much more dated that the photos on their websites made it look, but hey, I probably should have expected that given the place is over a hundred years old. Here's a summary of my experience:- Hotel check in: Went very smoothly. We arrived much earlier than the 3pm check-in time (we arrived at 11am), but the clerk checked us in promptly without question. She didn't even charge us any extra for the additional friend we brought, which was very nice. The best part of the check-in are the apples! There are complimentary apples for the guests at the front desk. These are the best apples I have ever tasted! Simple, but great idea on their part.-Hotel room: A little smaller than usual, but nevertheless clean and comfortable. The flat screen tv was a nice updated touch. We had problems turning the tv on when we arrived, and the front desk sent up someone immediately to have it fixed. Our view looked out into a stone-filled pit in the middle of the hotel, so it wasn't a great view, but unless you plan to look out the windown 24-7, this was really a non-issue. The beds had clean sheets with lots of comfy pillow to prop yourself up so you can watch TV in bed. The bathroom was clean, but definitely looked dated with some discolorations on the ceiling and the tub. Don't mistake this with it not being clean. The toilet was slower-flushing, but worked fine. The bathroom amenities included your usual lotions/shampoo/conditioner-but also bottled water! This was replenished by the maid daily. There were actually two hairdryers in the room, one in the washroom and the other in the cupboards under the TV. Also under the TV was the mini-fridge, which was empty. This was great for us because we would have never purchased from the mini-bar and it came in very handy for the storage of leftover foods and little extras we got at the nearby convenience stores.-Hotel Location: VERY VERY central. Don't bother cabbing from SFO as the BART station is 1 minute away from the hotel (5.35$ one-way). Bring your walking shoes because you can walk pretty much anywhere from this hotel. Lots of banks nearby, so its very safe as well. There are beggars on the street, but they aren't the types to hound you once you say no. We were there during the gay parade and the parade ran right in front of our hotel.-Hotel Amenities: Small workout facility and pool. There is about 10 cardio machines in total with some weights/weight machines right behind. All the equipment have TV attached, so bring some headphones. I didn't go into the, but it definitely looked a lot less majestic than it did in the photos. My friends tell me its good enough though.	
