Feb 13 2008 	Very grand good location	I just got back from staying at the Palace with my wife this past weekend. I knew going it was an older hotel with smaller rooms, and I wasn't sure about the location, so I was skeptical whether I would like the hotel. But I must say I was pleasantly surprised. The hotel was very grand. The lobby was much prettier than I expected. There was a big crowd checking in when we arrived but the front desk handled it smoothly and efficiently. Our room was larger than I anticipated. We had a king size bed, flat screen tv. , lounge chair and a desk that was sufficient for me to work from. The bathroom was small, but since I knew that going in, it wasn't a problem. But there was definitely no way more than one person at a time could be in the bathroom. The bed was comfortable and room quiet so I had no complaints. The only meals we had in the hotel were the breakfast buffet. The buffet was nothing spectacular but it was good. In addition to the usual scrambeled eggs, bacon and sausages, there were blintzes, waffles, pancakes etc. Nothing to complain about. The restaurant in which the buffet was served however was spectacular. The room reminded me very much of where they served the buffett at the Alvear Palace in Buenos Aires. For that matter the common areas of the hotel (not the guest rooms) reminded me of the Alvear. The location of the hotel worked out very nicely for us. It is in close walking distance to the convention center, china town, and good shopping. All in all a positive experience. The only negative comment either I or my wife had was that when she gave the concierge two packages already sealed with fed ex forms filled out and ready to go, the concierge charged her 5 dollars to out in the hotel's fed ex pickup. I thought a formal charge to basically put a package in the mail was kind of chintzy but nothing worth complaining about. I would stay there again.	
