Dec 18 2007 	Grand Old Hotel	We spent the weekend in San Francisco and wanted a hotel close to a BART station. We decided to fly into SFO and wanted to walk and use public transportation in SF because of the holiday traffic. We chose the Palace Hotel because it was located directly across the street from the Montgomery BART station. It is a lovely old grand hotel with a very European feel. We walked past the ornate and very busy bar to the efficient check in area as well as to the helpful concierge service. Our room was adequate, although the bathroom could have used some renovation....little counter space, plastic shower curtain over tub, and poor ventilation. The beds and bedding were comfy but next time I would make sure that I had a room with more efficient blackout curtains. Keep your voice down, though. We heard conversations on both sides of our room, so clearly some improvements need to be made. Breakfast in the ornate, gorgeous room was lovely and plentiful. The dining room and the entire hotel were decorated tastefully for the holidays. We enjoyed being able to walk to Union Square, the shopping area on Market Street, and to the MOMA. With just a few improvements, the Palace could become just that....a palace.	
