Oct 10 2007 	Loved the Palace!	We loved our stay at the Palace. Check in was easy and quick. Our room was on the 6th floor facing New Montgomery. The rooms are well appointed and very clean. The standard rooms are a bit small but the high ceilings really open the small space right up. It was perfect for 2 people. Concierge was helpful. Complimentary bottled water was left every day. The pool/spa/gym complex was very nice. There were always bowls of apples at the front desk. Coffee and papers were available every day. There was a City Guides free tour (they have them all over the city)at the hotel one morning, so we took it. It really gave you insight to the history of this opulent hotel and all the dignitaries that have stayed there over the years.I must say that I was really hesitant about staying at the Palace because of some previous reviews. I am glad to say that we had no problems at all. The city was easy to navigate from the Union Square area. We purchased a 3 day MUNI pass that we didn't even wind up using (other than to ride the cable car once) We walked everywhere and felt very safe even though there were lots of homeless people everywhere you went.	
Oct 10 2007 	Very nice stay even if room was small by today's standards	We chose the Palace due to it's location near the people we were visiting there. Overall, we were very pleased with our stay all the way from check in to check out. The only &quot;drawback&quot; is that with it being a hotel that was originally opened in the 19th century, the room, at least the one we stayed in on the 5th floor, is so tiny by today's standards some of you may feel a bit crowded. I believe most modern rooms in big hotels are at least 350 square feet. This room was smaller and the bathroom tiny. Still, everything worked out nice as far as the room was concerned. Room includes: Free bottles of water, robes, and the usual(blow dryer, iron, small tv). Service was polite and professional. Morning coffee and newspapers are provided. We did not eat in any hotel restaurants. The lobby is a nice place to relax and finish that coffee and paper. The location, as others mentioned, is somewhat less than wonderful from the standpoint that the homeless wander the streets pretty regularly. Still, we strolled the nearby streets at night so I would not say be fearful, just be prepared that people digging out of trash cans and holding a cup up to you will be pretty common. Also, you are only about a 15 minute walk from some of the touristy-sights, like the Ferry Plaza and Chinatown, and a rather tough two mile walk from the biggest draw to San Fran, the Fisherman's Wharf area. There is a nice indoor pool and jacuzzi. Unfortunately, the jacuzzi was out of order on the second day of our two day stay. I was a bit disappointed because this is the second time in the last couple of months a Starwood Chain hotel I stayed at has been been hampered by a broken hot tub. Oh well.. Our triple A room rate was $259/night plus about $36 dollars tax for a king size bed room. Note about charges: If you use a debit card, even with a VISA or Mastercard logo, to charge your room, the hotel charges you an extra $100 dollars per day for incidentals. Apparently, we were told the money is not credited back to you for 15 to 30 days. We checked-in using a credit card but paid with the debit card at check out and avoided those charges. We did not have a car so I do not know the parking charges. In summary, if you are a couple looking for a nice place and expect to be strolling the sights more than staying in the room, the Palace should be fine. But based on the size of the room, I would suggest parties of more than 2 compare the room size to other places first. .	
