Aug 28 2007 	Lovely Hotel Expensive Phone Calls!!!!!	As a former San Franciscan, I have always wanted to stay in this gorgeous hotel. I finally got the chance ! The rooms were very nice, and quiet. Honestly, we didn't encounter much service, as we are very familiar with this area of the city, and didn't require help navigating. The rooms are fairly austere, but very high quality, and very comfortable. This may sound odd, but the air conditioner was very quiet and the air felt clean.The Pied Piper Room with its Maxfield Parrish mural, and rich wood interior is not to be missed. I went there for drinks when I lived in SF, as well as each time I have returned home. The truffle french fries rock!The hotel is in the Financial District, so be aware that during the weekend a lot of restaurants in the immediate area are closed, or have limited hours. For those concerned about coffee (and believe me, I AM concerned about coffee) there is a Starbucks about a half block away on Montgomery, and place called Specialy's about 3/4 blocks down @ Montgomery &amp; Mission. They have coffee, pastry, and are known for their excellent cookies and bread. On the other side of Market St. on New Montgomery, there is another Starbucks as well as Peets Coffee, and Tulley's coffee in the Crocker Galleria.If you are staying at the hotel during the week, consider lunch at Belden Lane , a small street in the Financial District that has several great restaurants (French, Spanish &amp; Italian). If it's warm, you can eat outside. Belden Place is about 4 blocks from the hotel, and out of awful Union Square, where oddly, there is not much good fare.On to the bad news about the hotel....$17 PER COMPUTER/ PER DAY for internet service. Now, c'mon --There is something very wrong for a hotel of this caliber in tech saavy SF to charge for internet at all! Why don't they have wireless??? A 17 minute long distance phone call was $47. The cell phone reception in the room was not great, and we had to make an important phone call to the tune of $47. We had to send a fax from the business center which was grossly expensive (I'm not sure, I think that it was $8 per page),and the woman at the business center was less than pleasant with her huffy-puffy attitude. All in all, this is a beautiful hotel, in the best location, and most importantly, the best public restrooms in the city.	
