Jul 29 2006	Great Hotel in Great City	We stayed for 3 nights, midweek in late July 06. We arrived for early check in and our room wasn't available so we went to the Pied Piper Lounge for lunch. The history of the hotel is amazing and the painting in the Pied Piper Lounge is gorgeous. The entire hotel has been refurbished, but still maintains the classy elegance of its period. The crabcake was super good as was our salads. Our room was well above average in size and accomodations. We were in a junior suite. The closet was a large walk in with a safe and dresser incl. There was a nice sitting area as well. The bathroom was small but had plenty of counterspace which I find extremely important. We were on the 7th floor. There wasn't any great view. We looked at the offices across the street. We did find it extremely quiet well into mid morning which was quite refreshing. We took the advice of the concierge and ate at some pretty decent restaurants. I wouldn' t call any spectactular except for the Dim Sum restaurant (Yang Sing??) less than 1 block away...we ate there twice...it was that good!! Otherwise, the Italian restaurants on the concierge list may need to be reconsidered for recommendation. Shopping near Union Square is very accessible on foot. It was less than a 10 min. walk and we were in the thick of all of the great shops. From there we took the cable car down to the Wharf and Ghiradelli sq. etc. You can also walk to Chinatown if you are up to it. We found that we would walk around, have dinner then cab it back to the hotel. The city is really easy to navigate. The trip to Alcatraz was a big hit with the kids and I strongly suggest that you book early (before you arrive to SF) as they were sold out a week or two in advance for us. We had to buy the 2 island pass and skip Angel Island in order to visit Alcatraz (which was 2 x the reg. price). So reserve early so you aren't disappointed. The headset tour was a must as well. We really enjoyed the Palace Hotel. We enjoyed it's classy charm and nature and felt well treated by all staff. We would definitely stay there again and would recommend to friends too.	
