Sep 30 2004	A Fun Poltergeist Good Location Nice Stay	The Palace hotel is in a perfect location. I'll get to the ghost story later. It is old, and so are the loud noisy pipes. Our room was small, but the high ceilings helped to make it not-so cramped. The lobby staff did give off the impression that I was being snubbed a little. Parking at $40 a night is joke, around the corner you can pay $16, but even that is a scam. Every garage sets a daily rate from 6am-6am. If you stay one night, you pay for 2 full days=$32. So to the Ghost story, accross the bar is a bathroom. During the stay I went several times there. This time as I went to wash my hands, it was perfect timing as I walked to the door it automatically opened. I looked around and saw nothing that would open the door, and it never did that before. As I washed my hands, I saw in the mirror the door was still wide open. In the instant I turned around to dry my hands, I looked at the door and it was completely closed. I asked the doorman the next day if there were any ghosts in the place he said NO, I told him what happened, and he said, &quot;wellllllll, Some things have known to happen in the hall off the lobby near the bar&quot;. We would probably stay there again, but there are soooo many hotels in SF.	
